# Paginating GitHub API Responses

List endpoints return subsets of results. You must paginate to retrieve complete datasets.

## REST Pagination

### Link Headers

REST list endpoints return `Link` headers with URLs for navigation:

```http
Link: <https://api.github.com/repos/owner/repo/issues?page=2>; rel="next",
      <https://api.github.com/repos/owner/repo/issues?page=5>; rel="last"
```

Relation types: `next`, `prev`, `first`, `last`. Follow `rel="next"` until it's absent.

### Page-Based Parameters

| Parameter | Default | Max | Description |
|-----------|---------|-----|-------------|
| `per_page` | 30 | 100 | Items per page |
| `page` | 1 | ŌĆö | Page number |

```bash
# Page 1 with 100 items per page
curl -H "Authorization: Bearer $GITHUB_TOKEN" \
     "https://api.github.com/repos/owner/repo/issues?per_page=100&page=1"

# gh CLI with pagination
gh api repos/owner/repo/issues --paginate
```

### Octokit Auto-Pagination

```javascript
import { Octokit } from "@octokit/rest";

const octokit = new Octokit({ auth: process.env.GITHUB_TOKEN });

// Automatic pagination ŌĆö fetches ALL pages
const allIssues = await octokit.paginate(octokit.issues.listForRepo, {
  owner: "my-org",
  repo: "my-project",
  state: "open",
  per_page: 100,
});
console.log(`Fetched ${allIssues.length} issues`);

// With per-page callback for streaming
for await (const response of octokit.paginate.iterator(
  octokit.issues.listForRepo,
  { owner: "my-org", repo: "my-project", per_page: 100 }
)) {
  for (const issue of response.data) {
    console.log(issue.number, issue.title);
  }
}

// Map/filter during pagination
const issueTitles = await octokit.paginate(
  octokit.issues.listForRepo,
  { owner: "my-org", repo: "my-project", per_page: 100 },
  (response) => response.data.map((issue) => issue.title)
);
```

### Manual Link Header Parsing

```javascript
async function fetchAllPages(url, token) {
  const results = [];
  let nextUrl = url;

  while (nextUrl) {
    const response = await fetch(nextUrl, {
      headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` },
    });
    const data = await response.json();
    results.push(...data);

    // Parse Link header for next page
    const linkHeader = response.headers.get("Link");
    const nextMatch = linkHeader?.match(/<([^>]+)>;\s*rel="next"/);
    nextUrl = nextMatch ? nextMatch[1] : null;
  }

  return results;
}

const allIssues = await fetchAllPages(
  "https://api.github.com/repos/owner/repo/issues?per_page=100",
  process.env.GITHUB_TOKEN
);
```

## GraphQL Cursor Pagination

GraphQL uses the Relay connection pattern with opaque cursors:

```graphql
query($owner: String!, $name: String!, $cursor: String) {
  repository(owner: $owner, name: $name) {
    issues(first: 100, after: $cursor, states: OPEN) {
      totalCount
      pageInfo {
        hasNextPage
        endCursor
      }
      nodes {
        number
        title
      }
    }
  }
}
```

```javascript
import { graphql } from "@octokit/graphql";

const graphqlWithAuth = graphql.defaults({
  headers: { authorization: `token ${process.env.GITHUB_TOKEN}` },
});

async function fetchAllIssues(owner, name) {
  const issues = [];
  let cursor = null;
  let hasNextPage = true;

  while (hasNextPage) {
    const { repository } = await graphqlWithAuth(`
      query($owner: String!, $name: String!, $cursor: String) {
        repository(owner: $owner, name: $name) {
          issues(first: 100, after: $cursor, states: OPEN) {
            pageInfo { hasNextPage endCursor }
            nodes { number title }
          }
        }
      }
    `, { owner, name, cursor });

    issues.push(...repository.issues.nodes);
    hasNextPage = repository.issues.pageInfo.hasNextPage;
    cursor = repository.issues.pageInfo.endCursor;
  }

  return issues;
}
```

### Forward vs. Backward Pagination

| Direction | Arguments | PageInfo Fields |
|-----------|-----------|------------------|
| Forward | `first`, `after` | `hasNextPage`, `endCursor` |
| Backward | `last`, `before` | `hasPreviousPage`, `startCursor` |

## gh CLI Pagination

The `gh` CLI supports automatic pagination:

```bash
# --paginate fetches all pages and combines results
gh api repos/owner/repo/issues --paginate -q '.[].title'

# Limit to specific number of results with --jq
gh api repos/owner/repo/issues --paginate --jq '.[:50] | .[].title'

# GraphQL pagination with gh
gh api graphql --paginate -f query='
  query($endCursor: String) {
    repository(owner: "owner", name: "repo") {
      issues(first: 100, after: $endCursor) {
        pageInfo { hasNextPage endCursor }
        nodes { number title }
      }
    }
  }
'
```
